Won't let me edit the page since I'm a new account, but I have a Java solution for 
Replay a shuffled deck. Add a menu option to replay the last "shuffled" game.

<syntaxhighlight lang="java">
    public Main() {
        char choice;
        TCard[] deck = new TCard[53];
        TRecentScore[] recentScores = new TRecentScore[NO_OF_RECENT_SCORES + 1];
        for (int count = 1; count <= NO_OF_RECENT_SCORES; count++) {
            recentScores[count] = new TRecentScore();
            recentScores[count].name = "";
            recentScores[count].score = 0;
        }
        do {
            displayMenu();
            choice = getMenuChoice();
            switch (choice) {
                case '1':
                loadDeck(deck);
                shuffleDeck(deck);
                playGame(deck, recentScores);
                break;
                case '2':
                loadDeck(deck);
                playGame(deck, recentScores);
                break;
                case '3':
                displayRecentScores(recentScores);
                break;
                case '4':
                resetRecentScores(recentScores);
                break;  
                case '5':
                loadDeck(deck);
                playLastGame(deck);
                playGame(deck, recentScores);
                break;
            }
        } while (choice != 'q');
    }

    void displayMenu() {
        console.println();
        console.println("MAIN MENU");
        console.println();
        console.println("1.  Play game (with shuffle)");
        console.println("2.  Play game (without shuffle)");
        console.println("3.  Display recent scores");
        console.println("4.  Reset recent scores");
        console.println("5.  Play using the last shuffled deck");
        console.println();
        console.print("Select an option from the menu (or enter q to quit): ");
    }

    void shuffleDeck(TCard[] deck) {
        int noOfSwaps;
        int position1;
        int position2;
        TCard swapSpace;
        swapSpace = new TCard();
        int noOfSwapsMadeSoFar;
        noOfSwaps = 1000;
        for (noOfSwapsMadeSoFar = 1; noOfSwapsMadeSoFar <= noOfSwaps; noOfSwapsMadeSoFar++) {
            position1 = random.nextInt(52) + 1;
            position2 = random.nextInt(52) + 1;
            swapSpace.rank = deck[position1].rank;
            swapSpace.suit = deck[position1].suit;
            deck[position1].rank = deck[position2].rank;
            deck[position1].suit = deck[position2].suit;
            deck[position2].rank = swapSpace.rank;
            deck[position2].suit = swapSpace.suit;
        }
        AQAWriteTextFile2014 writefile = new AQAWriteTextFile2014("previousdeck.txt", false);
        for (int i = 1; i < deck.length; i++) {
            writefile.writeToTextFile(String.valueOf(deck[i].rank));
            writefile.writeToTextFile(String.valueOf(deck[i].suit));
        }
        writefile.closeFile();
    }

    void playLastGame(TCard[] deck) {
        AQAReadTextFile2014 readfile = new AQAReadTextFile2014("previousdeck.txt");
        String line = "";
        for (int i = 1; i < deck.length; i++) {
            line = readfile.readLine();
            deck[i].rank = Integer.valueOf(line);
            line = readfile.readLine();
            deck[i].suit = Integer.valueOf(line);
        }
        readfile.closeFile();
    }

</syntaxhighlight>

Also have one for When the card number is the same you draw and go onto the next card instead of losing.

<syntaxhighlight lang="java">
    void playGame(TCard[] deck, TRecentScore[] recentScores) {
        int noOfCardsTurnedOver;
        boolean gameOver;
        TCard nextCard;
        TCard lastCard;
        nextCard = new TCard();
        lastCard = new TCard();
        boolean higher;
        char choice;
        gameOver = false;
        getCard(lastCard, deck, 0);
        displayCard(lastCard);
        noOfCardsTurnedOver = 1;
        while (noOfCardsTurnedOver < 52 && !gameOver) {
            getCard(nextCard, deck, noOfCardsTurnedOver);
            do {
                choice = getChoiceFromUser();
            } while (!(choice == 'y' || choice == 'n'));
            displayCard(nextCard);
            noOfCardsTurnedOver = noOfCardsTurnedOver + 1;
            higher = isNextCardHigher(lastCard, nextCard);
            if (lastCard.rank == nextCard.rank) { // Check if draw
                wasDraw(noOfCardsTurnedOver - 1);
                lastCard.rank = nextCard.rank;
                lastCard.suit = nextCard.suit;
            } else if (higher && choice =='y' || !higher && choice=='n') {
                displayCorrectGuessMessage(noOfCardsTurnedOver - 1);
                lastCard.rank = nextCard.rank;
                lastCard.suit = nextCard.suit;
            } else {
                gameOver = true;
            }
        }
        if (gameOver) {
            displayEndOfGameMessage(noOfCardsTurnedOver - 2);
            updateRecentScores(recentScores, noOfCardsTurnedOver - 2);
        } else {
            displayEndOfGameMessage(51);
            updateRecentScores(recentScores, 51);
        }
    }

    void wasDraw(int score) {
        console.println("It's a draw! You get a free point.");
        console.printf("Your score is now %s.\r\n", score);
        console.println();
    }
</syntaxhighlight>
[[User:DanFoad|DanFoad]] ([[User talk:DanFoad|discuss]] • [[Special:Contributions/DanFoad|contribs]]) 15:42, 29 April 2014 (UTC)

==Motion== Force interacts with matter to make matter move creates Motion
==Motion's Characteristics== All motion has the following characteristics * [[Distance]] , measurement of how far matter travels . Distance is denoted as <math>s</math> and measured in <math>m</math> . * [[Speed]] , measurement of how fast matter travels . Speed is denoted as <math>v</math> , measured in <math>\frac{m}{s}</math> . * [[Acceleration]] , measurement of how fast matter travels . Acceleration is denoted as <math>a</math> , measured in <math>\frac{m}{s^2}</math> . * [[Force]], measurement of strength . Force is denoted as <math>F</math> , measured in <math>N</math> . * [[Work]], measurement of Force's capability to do perform a task on matter . Work is denoted as <math>W</math> , measured in <math>N m</math>. * [[Energy]], measurement of how work is done over a time period . Energy is denoted as <math>E</math> and measured in <math>N \frac{m}{s}</math>
==Motion's types== ===Linear Motion=== Motion of matter that follows a straight line :{| class="prettytable" width=100% align=center ! Characteristics !! Symbol!! Formula!! Unit |- | Speed || <math>v</math> || <math>\frac{s}{t}</math> ||<math>\frac{m}{s}</math> |- | Acceleration || <math>a</math> || <math>\frac{v}{t}</math> || <math>\frac{m}{s^2}</math> |- | Distance || <math>s</math> || <math>v t</math> || <math>m</math> |- | Force ||<math> F</math> || <math>m a</math> || <math>N </math> |- | Work || <math>W</math> || <math>F s</math> || <math>N m</math> |- | Energy || <math>E</math> || <math>\frac{W}{t}</math> || <math>N \frac{m}{s}</math> |- |}
===Non Linear Motion=== Matter's motion does not follow a straight line
:{| class="prettytable" width=100% align=center ! Tính Chất Chuyển Động !! Ký Hiệu !! Công Thức Đạo Hàm , Tích Phân |- | Speed || v || <math> v(t)</math> |- | acceleration || a || <math>\frac{dv(t)}{dt} = \frac{d^2s(t)}{dt^2}</math> |- | Distance || s || <math>\int v(t) dt</math> |- | Force || F || <math>m \frac{dv(t)}{dt}</math> |- | Work || W || <math>F \int v(t) dt</math> |- | Energy || E || <math>\frac {F}{t} \int v(t) dt</math> |- |}
===Periodic Motion=== Matter's motion repeats iself over a period of time :{| class="prettytable" width=100% align=center ! Characteristics!! Symbol !! Formula |- | Distance|| <math>s</math> || <math>2 \pi</math> |- | Speed || <math>v</math> ||<math>\frac{2\pi}{t}</math> |- | Angular Speed || <math> \omega</math> ||<math>2 \pi f</math> |- | Frequency || f ||<math>f = \frac{1}{t}</math> |}
===Momentum=== A Mass travels at a Speed :{| class="prettytable" width=100% align=center ! Characteristics !! Symbol !! Formula !! Unit |- | Momentum || <math>p</math> || <math>m v </math> ||<math>kg \frac{m}{s}</math> |- | Impulse || <math>F</math> || <math>m a = m \frac{v}{t} = \frac{p}{t}</math> || <math>\frac{m}{s^2}</math> |- | Work || <math>W</math> || <math>F s = F v t = p v</math> || <math>m</math> |- | Energy|| <math>E</math> || <math>\frac{W}{t} = F \frac{s}{t} = F v = F a t = p a</math> || <math>N \frac{m}{s}</math> |- |}
===Oscillation=== Movement of matter about an equilibrium position over a period of time : [[Tập_tin:Simple_harmonic_oscillator.gif|50px]]
At equilibrium : <math>F = - F_y</math> : <math>m a = -ky</math> : <math>m \frac{d^2y}{dt^2} = -ky</math> : <math> \frac{d^2y}{dt^2} + \frac{k}{m}y = 0 </math> : <math>s = \pm j \sqrt{\frac{k}{m}}</math> : <math>y = A Sin \omega t</math> : <math> \omega = \pm j (\sqrt{\frac{k}{m}}t)</math> : [[File:Wave.png|200px]]
: [[T%E1%BA%ADp_tin:Simple_pendulum_height.png|200px]] : <math>m g = -l y</math> : <math>y = \frac{m g}{l}</math> = v t : <math>t =\frac{m g}{l v}</math>
# ''Dao động là chuyển động tuần hoàn quanh vị trí cân bằng'' . # ''Mọi dao động điều hòa có thể biểu diễn thành phương trình đạo hàm bậc hai với nghiệm ảo'' # ''Dao động điều hòa có thể coi như một sóng lan truyền với vận tốc lan truyền bằng tích của bước sóng và tần số'' # ''Dao động điều hòa có thể biểu diển bằng hàm số toán của sóng sin'
===Wave=== A periodic oscillation travels in space : [[Image:wave.png|300px|A wave with constant amplitude.]]
:{| class="prettytable" width=100% align=center ! Wave !! Symbol !! Formula |- | Distance || s || <math>\lambda</math> |- | Speed || v || <math>\frac{\lambda}{t}</math> |- | Angular Speed || <math>\omega</math> || <math>\lambda f</math> |- | Frequency || f || <math>\frac{1}{t}</math> |- | Equation || f || <math>\frac{1}{t}</math> |- | Function || f(t) || <math>A Sin \omega t</math> |- |}
===Relative Motion=== Motion of matter at speed of light
Momentum travels at speed of light :<math>pC = h \frac{C}{\lambda}</math> :<math>\lambda = \frac{h}{p}</math>
Wave travels at speed of light :<math>v = C = \lambda f</math> :<math>\lambda = \frac{C}{f}</math> :<math>f = \frac{C}{\lambda}</math>
Photon :<math>hnf_o = h \frac{C}{\lambda}</math>
